---
alwaysApply: true
---

Folder & layer structure:
- Project is organized by architectural layers, not by feature folders.
- Clean Architecture layers are required:
  - domain
  - application
  - infrastructure
  - presentation
- Domain logic must never depend on outer layers.

Domain organization:
- Domain folders represent business concepts (e.g. user, order).
- Domain contains entities and repository interfaces only.

File naming conventions:
- camelCase is used inside code (variables, functions, methods).
- Filenames do NOT use camelCase.
- Filenames use dot-notation to express responsibility:
  - *.entity.ts
  - *.service.ts
  - *.repository.ts
  - *.controller.ts
  - *.schema.ts
- Folder expresses architectural layer and domain.
- Filename expresses role within that layer.

Important:
- Do NOT collapse multiple layers into a single folder.
- Examples of filenames do NOT imply a flat folder structure.
